=== TASK ===
# Landing Page

## Overview
Build a production-ready public Landing Page for Archject that clearly introduces the product, highlights core features and differentiators, provides pricing CTAs, social proof, and directs visitors to sign up or request a demo. This deliverable also includes related public/legal/support pages (About/Help, Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, 404) and assets/functional hooks required for branding/custom client links, onboarding/demo content, and authentication entry points.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Landing Page is the public-facing marketing entry point for Archject — a visual approval and decision-logging platform for architecture and design studios. Its primary goals are: explain the product value quickly, demonstrate core features and differentiators (visual decisions, client-facing links, audit logs, templates/exports), collect user interest (Get Started / Book Demo), and funnel studios to sign up or request a demo. The Landing Page must integrate visually and functionally with Branding & Custom Client Links (descriptive UI and signup flows leading to studio branding settings), surface App Logo & Icon assets, and reference Onboarding & Demo Assets for trial accounts.

Key UI elements:
- Top navigation: logo (left), links (Product/How it works/Pricing/About/Help), primary CTA (Get Started), secondary CTA (Book Demo). Mobile-friendly hamburger navigation.
- Hero section: H1 headline, supporting paragraph/value bullets, primary CTA (Get Started) and secondary CTA (Book Demo), hero image or short looping GIF/video showing side-by-side option reviews on mobile + desktop.
- Feature highlights: horizontally arranged cards (Visual Decisions, Client Link, Audit Logs, Templates, Exports) with icons, 1–2 sentence descriptions, CTA to learn more.
- How it Works: 3-step visual flow with illustrations: Create Decision → Share Link → Get Approval & Export. Each step has short copy and a small illustrative card.
- Pricing teaser: condensed 3-tier summary (e.g., Free Trial, Studio, Enterprise) with quick bullets and CTA to full pricing/billing in-app.
- Social proof: customer logos grid (muted), 1–2 highlighted testimonials with photo/name/role, “As seen in / Trusted by” line.
- Footer: link cluster (Help, About, Privacy, Terms, Contact/Support), app logo and small copyright + social links.
- Login/Signup link: present in header and in footer; CTA routes to the unified Login/Signup page supporting SSO/OAuth.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, keyboard focus states, ARIA where appropriate, color contrast checks.

API integrations:
- No external product APIs required for static marketing content. However, the page needs endpoints to:
  - Submit demo requests (POST /api/lead/demo) — stores lead and optionally triggers email notification.
  - Newsletter or waitlist signup (POST /api/lead/signup).
  - Link to pricing/billing in-app (public URL /pricing or route to Settings/Billing once authenticated).
  - Redirects to Login/Signup page to begin studio onboarding.
- Branding & Custom Client Links: include descriptive UI and a call-to-action leading authenticated studio users to their Branding settings. Provide example JSON for how a studio’s branding will be represented publicly (logo, color, domain) for client links.

Visual guidance: follow provided Visual Style, color palette, typographic scale, 12-column grid, card and button styles. Use accent #0052CC sparingly. Ensure responsive mobile-first layout.

## Components to Build
- Header (responsive) with navigation, primary CTA (Get Started), secondary CTA (Book Demo), and Login link.
- Hero component: headline, subcopy, CTA buttons, illustrative media (image/video).
- FeatureCards component: five feature cards with icon + title + description + small CTA.
- HowItWorks component: 3-step flow with step cards and illustrations.
- PricingTeaser component: condensed tier cards with CTA linking to /pricing or signup modal.
- Testimonials component: carousel or responsive grid of quotes + logos.
- SocialProofLogos: muted logo grid.
- Footer: multi-column link set, copyright, small nav.
- DemoSubmission form + API client (frontend).
- Sign-up / Login CTA component hooking to authentication routes.
- Legal/Public pages: About/Help, Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, 404 Not Found page, Login/Signup page — styled to match design system.
- Branding preview callout: small interactive preview showing how white-label client links appear (logo, color swatch, custom domain example).
- Asset integration: App Logo & Icon set, favicon, and Onboarding & Demo Assets placeholders used in hero or demo request flows.
- Meta and SEO: structured meta tags, Open Graph, Twitter Card, JSON-LD Organization markup (logo, url, contact), canonical URL.
- Analytics events: track clicks on CTAs (Get Started, Book Demo), demo form submissions, newsletter signups.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework: Next.js (recommended) or single-page React. Pages under /pages or /app to support SSR and SEO.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS or CSS-in-JS (emotion/styled-components) implementing color palette & typographic scale. Use a 12-column responsive grid system.
- Components:
  - Header: responsive, accessible navigation. Desktop shows full nav; mobile uses a slide-over menu. CTA buttons per design system (primary #0052CC).
  - Hero: large H1 (28px equivalent), supporting paragraph, CTAs (primary solid, secondary outline), media (lazy-loaded image or autoplay muted short MP4/WebM). CTA primary to /signup; Book Demo opens demo request modal or route.
  - FeatureCards: accessible cards with icons (SVGs), short copy, hover states, keyboard focus style.
  - HowItWorks: horizontal flow on desktop, stacked on mobile; use numbered badges and connecting dashed line.
  - PricingTeaser: 3 small cards with price/benefit bullets; each card includes CTA to /pricing or sign-up. For Enterprise show “Contact Sales” CTA opens demo form.
  - SocialProof: logos grayscale, testimonials with avatar, name, role, quote.
  - Footer: links to About/Help, Privacy, Terms, Contact. Small site map for crawlers.

- Forms:
  - DemoRequestForm: fields: name, studio name, email (required), phone (optional), studio size, message. Client-side validation, accessibility labels, success and error states.
  - Newsletter/Waitlist: email-only input with validation.
  - Forms must show 1–3 inline validation messages and a success toast/modal on submit.

- Accessibility:
  - All buttons and links keyboard-focusable.
  - Alt text for all images.
  - Proper ARIA attributes for modals and forms.
  - Color contrast meets WCAG AA.

- Responsive behavior:
  - Mobile-first styles. Breakpoints: mobile (<640px), tablet (640–1024px), desktop (>=1024px).
  - Navigation and hero media adapt for mobile (use smaller images or crop).

### Backend
- Language/Framework: Node.js + Express or Next.js API routes (recommended).
- Persistence: Small relational table(s) in PostgreSQL or NoSQL in MongoDB for leads and demo requests. Optional integration with CRM webhook.
- Endpoints:
  - POST /api/leads/demo — store demo request and send email to sales/support (via SendGrid/SES).
  - POST /api/leads/signup — newsletter/demo waitlist signup.
  - GET /api/branding/:studioId/preview — returns public branding data (logo URL, primary color hex, custom domain if set). This is read-only public endpoint used to render Branding Preview for unauthenticated visitors (if showing examples).
- Email notifications: trigger transactional email for demo requests and confirmation email to requester.
- Rate limiting and spam prevention: basic recaptcha v3 or honeypot + server-side rate-limit.

Database tables (minimum):
- leads: id, type ('demo'|'signup'), name, email, studio_name, phone, message, studio_size, created_at, ip_address, utm_source, status.
- branding_public_preview (or table in studios): studio_id, logo_url, logo_alt_text, primary_color_hex, custom_domain, created_at, updated_at.
- assets: (optional) store references to Onboarding & Demo Assets: id, type, url, meta.

### Integration
- Demo form -> POST /api/leads/demo -> store in DB -> send email to sales + webhook to Slack or CRM.
- Signups -> POST /api/leads/signup -> store -> optionally send welcome email.
- Branding Preview component queries GET /api/branding/:studioId/preview for real studio examples shown in marketing copy or demos.
- Login/Signup CTA -> navigates to /auth (unified Login/Signup page) which uses existing auth backend (JWT or OAuth). Ensure route supports SSO buttons and password reset link.
- Link to Terms/Privacy -> static pages rendered server-side for SEO and legal compliance.
- Onboarding & Demo Assets: provide a script/seed API (or admin tool) to populate trial accounts with sample project data and assets; Landing page may link to a demo account video or screenshots.

## User Experience Flow
1. Visitor lands on home page. Hero communicates value and shows CTA.
2. Visitor clicks Get Started:
   - If authenticated: redirected to workspace creation or Billing/Signup flow.
   - If unauthenticated: sent to /auth (signup/login). Offer SSO/OAuth options and "Book Demo" alternative.
3. Visitor clicks Book Demo: opens modal form to collect details -> on submit, show success state, send email to sales, redirect optionally to calendar scheduling or thank-you page.
4. Visitor scrolls to feature sections and How It Works. Clicks “See branded client link example” -> branding preview modal shows logo/color/domain example using branding preview API sample.
5. Visitor clicks Pricing CTA -> /pricing page or pricing modal with links to sign-up.
6. Links to About/Help, Privacy, Terms available in footer and header. About/Help page contains documentation links and contact support.
7. If visitor follows a broken link, 404 page shows, suggests primary routes (Home, Pricing, Help, Login) and has search box.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - leads
    - id: uuid (PK)
    - type: enum('demo','signup')
    - name: varchar(255)
    - email: varchar(320)
    - studio_name: varchar(255) nullable
    - phone: varchar(50) nullable
    - studio_size: varchar(50) nullable
    - message: text nullable
    - utm_source: varchar(255) nullable
    - ip_address: inet nullable
    - status: enum('new','contacted') default 'new'
    - created_at: timestamp
  - studios (excerpt for branding)
    - id: uuid (PK)
    - name: varchar(255)
    - branding_logo_url: varchar(2048) nullable
    - branding_logo_alt: varchar(255) nullable
    - branding_primary_color: varchar(7) nullable
    - branding_custom_domain: varchar(255) nullable
    - branding_enabled: boolean default false
  - assets
    - id: uuid
    - type: enum('logo','favicon','demo_image','pdf')
    - url: varchar(2048)
    - meta: jsonb
    - created_at: timestamp

- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/leads/demo
    - Body: { name, email, studioName?, phone?, studioSize?, message?, utmSource? }
    - Returns: 201 { id, message }
  - POST /api/leads/signup
    - Body: { email, utmSource? }
    - Returns: 201 { id, message }
  - GET /api/branding/:studioId/preview
    - Returns: 200 { studioId, name, logoUrl, logoAlt, primaryColor, customDomain }
  - GET /sitemap.xml and GET /robots.txt — SEO friendly
  - GET /api/health — health check
  - (Auth routes for /auth managed by existing auth system)

- Security:
  - CSRF protection for forms (if server-side rendered forms).
  - Input sanitization and server-side validation.
  - Rate-limiting on lead endpoints (e.g., 5 requests per IP per minute).
  - Recaptcha v3 or honeypot anti-bot on demo/signup forms.
  - HTTPS-only cookies, secure headers (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, CSP).
  - For branding preview endpoint, return only public-facing fields. No internal studio secrets.

- Validation:
  - name: required for demo, 2–100 chars.
  - email: required, RFC-compliant, max 320 chars.
  - studioName: optional, max 255.
  - phone: optional, digits + typical punctuation, max 50.
  - message: max 2000 chars.
  - email uniqueness not required for leads; deduplicate server-side if necessary.
  - For color hex values: regex /^#([A-Fa-f0-9]{6}|[A-Fa-f0-9]{3})$/.

